                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d177">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">810.20 Defense/2721: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lane</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-05-29T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >May 29, 1942—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>627. The War Department and this Department have assumed that your reference to
                    entry of our forces in Colombian waters in your recent telegrams (687 and 700)
                    still means “Colombian waters or territories” as in the first paragraph of your
                    666, approved in the Department’s 591.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
